I stand for legalizing and decriminalizing sex work (I’m taking in general, not just about nude photos). Yes, there are some creeps in the world, some really bad people. But if a safe system is set in place, and made accessible to those who seek out anything sexual, then that could help curb underground sex trafficking or even rape.
I think that many people are apprehensive towards the idea of sex work because they view it as special, something intimate or sacred - especially if one has a religious background (it could come off as wrong to promote sex out of wedlock.)
Others though, they just wanna have fun with it. Some people just want casual sex with no strings attached. And in this day and age, we have birth control and condoms to help stop pregnancy and the spread of STD’s.
If that lady goes along with her plan and makes a very thorough system for safe sex work, I support it. Like screening clients seeking out sex services (to make sure they are not offenders or anything bad like that), and making sure that the sex workers themselves are of age & treated fairly. If that happens, I’m all for it. If you are against it, that’s ok. However I don’t think there is a need to shame someone for wanting to do sex work. It’s their body, their wants/needs, and hell, if they feel sexy, let them be.

(This is just an opinion, would love to discuss this more if anyone wants! I don’t intent to hate on people who disagree, nor want to encourage illegal sex trafficking of any sort.)

snippet.textDisplay: It might all be by the books and legal, but any traffic to OnlyFans is only strengthening the platform that really does enable human trafficking from others. If we as a culture were to figure out the issue of sex, it would have a huge impact on child poverty rates, homelessness, disease, human trafficking, and so much more. I'm not saying we all need to be prudes, but the dominance of PornHub and ever-rising success of OnlyFans and other sites simply highlights an utter failure by our culture to grapple with sex properly.

snippet.textDisplay:
I get the whole only fans thing... but its kind of weird to me. Basically if your really attractive you dont have to get a job. You can just sell your photos online until your old enough that people stop following/buying. What about their kids? They will have no experience to pass down, they wont have a work ethic. It just seems harmful in the big picture of things.

I understand how the world has influencers and creators but this is trying to expand to such a broad market its becoming a problem, in my opinion at least. Maybe too many girls will flood the market and dry up the income source, leading to the death of this industry after a handful of people blow up from it. just maybe.

Another point to add is the fact that you shouldn't confuse the tax the sex workers pay since it is a form of penalty and not approval of such conduct.
